{
  "doc_id": "1801",
  "text": "The Coquimbo Region was the most affected by the tsunami. Authors such as [CITATION_1] indicate that the tsunami was diffracted and refracted by the Coquimbo Peninsula, and it then converged to the inner southwestern corner of Coquimbo Bay. In the bay, the maximum runup was 14 m in the Baquedano sector (Fig. 1) , whereas towards the north the run-up only reached < 0.5 m and, according to our reconstruction, the waves penetrated inland more than 950 m in the Elqui mouth and almost 700 m in Culebrón stream mouth, while in Coquimbo Port and Serena they only reached 100-200 m and ca. 30 m, respectively ( Fig. 2b  and c ).",
